      type: "story",
      title: "Leo and the Dinosaur Playmates",
      description: "A little boy named Leo discovers a magical treehouse where friendly dinosaurs invite him to play, teaching him the joy of friendship and imagination in a prehistoric world.",
      cover: "/covers/gen-d5bc0057ca40.svg",
      character: {"name": "Leo", "identity": "A gentle adventurer who finds magic in everyday moments", "special": "He can see and play with dinosaurs that others can’t, unlocking a hidden world", "personality_tags": ["Curious", "Playful"]},
      addedAt: "2026-02-23",
      mood: "curious",
      story_type: "folk_tale",
      text: "[GENTLE] High up in a tall, ancient tree, there was a cozy little treehouse. It belonged to a kind boy named Leo, who loved to climb and play there every day. The treehouse was warm and safe, with soft leaves for a roof and vines for walls. Leo often wondered what adventures awaited him beyond the branches.\n\n[CURIOUS] One evening, as the sun painted the sky with soft pinks and oranges, Leo heard a gentle rustling outside his treehouse. He peeked out and saw a tiny, colorful dinosaur with shiny scales. The dinosaur had big, friendly eyes and a smile that made Leo feel happy inside. 'Hello!' the dinosaur chirped. 'I’m Tilly. Would you like to play with us?'\n\n[EXCITED] Leo’s eyes widened with excitement. 'Us?' he asked. Just then, two more dinosaurs popped their heads out from behind the leaves. There was a big, gentle Brontosaurus named Benny, and a small, quick Velociraptor named Roxy. They all waved at Leo, their tails swishing with joy. 'We’ve been waiting for you!' Benny said in a deep, rumbling voice. 'Come play with us!'\n\n[ADVENTUROUS] Leo climbed down from his treehouse, his heart pounding with excitement. The dinosaurs led him to a magical clearing where the grass sparkled like tiny stars. There were flowers that glowed softly in the twilight, and fireflies danced in the air like little lanterns. 'This is our playground,' Roxy said, giggling. 'We come here to play every night!'\n\n[JOYFUL] Leo and his new friends played games together. They chased each other through the glowing flowers, and Benny used his long neck to lift Leo high into the air so he could touch the clouds. Tilly showed Leo how to make music by tapping on hollow logs, and Roxy taught him how to jump over tiny streams. Leo laughed and laughed, his heart filled with happiness. 'I’ve never had so much fun!' he said.\n\n[CALM] As the night grew deeper, the fireflies began to dim, and the stars twinkled brightly above. The dinosaurs gathered around Leo, their eyes soft and sleepy. 'It’s time for us to rest,' Benny said gently. 'But we’ll be here tomorrow night if you want to play again.' Leo nodded, feeling warm and cozy inside. He knew he had made friends who would always be there for him.\n\n[WHISPERING] Tilly leaned in and whispered, 'You know, Leo, the magic of this place comes from friendship. As long as we play together with kindness, the fun never ends.' Leo smiled, hugging his new friends tightly. He climbed back into his treehouse, his heart full of joy and his mind full of wonderful memories.\n\n[SLEEPY] As he snuggled into his soft leaf bed, Leo closed his eyes, dreaming of dinosaurs and glowing flowers. He knew that tomorrow would bring another adventure, and he couldn’t wait to see his friends again. With a happy sigh, Leo drifted off to sleep, feeling safe, loved, and ready for more magical playtime.",
      target_age: 3,
      duration: 4,
      like_count: 0,
      save_count: 0,
      view_count: 0,
      categories: ["Friendship", "Fantasy", "Prehistoric Adventure"],
