      type: "long_story",
      title: "Kai and the Colors of the Night",
      description: "A tiny firefly discovers the magic of Holi’s fading colors, learning to glow softly as the festival winds down into sweet sleep.",
      cover: "/covers/gen-e3e07799ab05.svg",
      addedAt: "2026-03-05",
      mood: "calm",
      story_type: "dream",
      text: "[GENTLE] The sky above the mango grove was painted in streaks of pink and gold. [PAUSE] Kai the firefly fluttered his tiny wings, just waking up. [PAUSE] The air smelled like warm sugar and flowers—Holi had been so much fun! [PAUSE] But now, the bonfire was just embers, glowing softly like a sleepy orange eye.\n\n[CURIOUS] Kai zoomed close to the ground. [PAUSE] What was that? [PAUSE] A puddle of water shimmered with swirls of blue and pink. [PAUSE] It looked like the gulal colors had danced right into the rain! [EXCITED] Kai dipped his wing into the puddle. [PAUSE] The water felt cool and tickly. [PAUSE] [CHAR_START]Oh! It’s still magic![CHAR_END] he giggled.\n\n[JOYFUL] He fluttered higher, his little light blinking on. [PAUSE] Below, the children were packing up their pichkaris, their clothes splashed with rainbow splotches. [PAUSE] A gujiya sweet rolled into the grass, and Kai landed beside it. [PAUSE] [CHAR_START]Mmm, still warm![CHAR_END] he said, nibbling the edge. [PAUSE] The sweetness made his whole body tingle.\n\n[CALM] Then, Kai noticed something new. [PAUSE] The colors weren’t just on the ground anymore. [PAUSE] They were floating in the air, like tiny sparkles of dust. [PAUSE] Pink, yellow, blue—all drifting slowly toward the trees. [PAUSE] [CHAR_START]Where are you going?[CHAR_END] Kai whispered.\n\n[GENTLE] A soft breeze answered, carrying the colors higher. [PAUSE] Kai followed, his wings humming gently. [PAUSE] The grove was quieter now. [PAUSE] The laughter had faded into the rustle of leaves. [PAUSE] Kai landed on a low branch, his light dimming just a little. [PAUSE] [CHAR_START]It’s time to rest,[CHAR_END] he thought.\n\n[PHASE_2]\n\n[CALM] Kai curled his wings around himself. [PAUSE] The branch was warm from the sun, and the bark felt bumpy but cozy. [PAUSE] [BREATH_CUE] He breathed in deep—whoosh—and out—ahhh—slow and steady. [PAUSE] His tiny body rose and fell like the gentle waves of the puddle below.\n\n[SLEEPY] [CHAR_START]I’ll stretch my wings wide,[CHAR_END] Kai murmured. [PAUSE] He stretched them out—so big!—then let them go floppy. [PAUSE] [BREATH_CUE] Another breath in—whoosh—and out—ahhh. [PAUSE] His light flickered, softer now, like a candle in the breeze.\n\n[SLEEPY] Kai yawned a great big yawn. [PAUSE] His jaw stretched wide, then closed with a little *click*. [PAUSE] His eyelids felt heavy, like they were made of the softest petals. [PAUSE] [BREATH_CUE] One more breath—whoosh—and out—ahhh. [PAUSE] The colors in the air were still drifting, but now they were settling, like a blanket over the grove.\n\n[CALM] [CHAR_START]I’ll curl up small,[CHAR_END] Kai whispered. [PAUSE] He tucked his wings tight and curled into a tiny ball. [PAUSE] The branch cradled him, warm and safe. [PAUSE] His light pulsed once, twice—then dimmed to a soft, steady glow. [PAUSE] [BREATH_CUE] In—whoosh—and out—ahhh. [PAUSE] The world felt very still.\n\n[PHASE_3]\n\n[SLEEPY] Warm... so warm... [LONG_PAUSE] Kai’s glow hummed softly, like a lullaby. [LONG_PAUSE] The colors in the air settled around him, pink and blue and gold. [LONG_PAUSE] They wrapped him up, gentle as a blanket. [LONG_PAUSE]\n\n[WHISPERING] Heavy... so heavy... [LONG_PAUSE] His wings felt like they were made of clouds. [LONG_PAUSE] His eyelids, like petals closing. [LONG_PAUSE] The breeze whispered through the leaves, shhh, shhh, shhh. [LONG_PAUSE]\n\n[WHISPERING] One light dimmed... [LONG_PAUSE] then another... [LONG_PAUSE] then another... [LONG_PAUSE] The grove was full of tiny glowing lights, all fading softly. [LONG_PAUSE] Kai’s light flickered once, twice—then glowed steady and low. [LONG_PAUSE]\n\n[WHISPERING] Safe... so safe... [LONG_PAUSE] The colors held him close. [LONG_PAUSE] The branch rocked him, slow and steady. [LONG_PAUSE] The night wrapped around him like a hug. [LONG_PAUSE]\n\n[WHISPERING] Sleep now... little one... [LONG_PAUSE] The colors whispered. [LONG_PAUSE] The breeze whispered. [LONG_PAUSE] The grove whispered. [LONG_PAUSE]\n\n[WHISPERING] Sleep... [LONG_PAUSE] sleep... [LONG_PAUSE] sleep... [LONG_PAUSE]",
      lullaby_lyrics: "[verse]\nKai’s light glows soft and low,\nPink and gold in evening’s glow.\nWings curled up, so warm, so tight,\nDancing colors say goodnight.\n\n[chorus]\nHush now, little firefly,\nDrift and dream beneath the sky.\nColors fade, the night is deep,\nTime to rest, time to sleep.\n\n[verse]\nPichkaris rest, the water’s still,\nGujiya sweet on window sill.\nBreeze hums soft, the stars shine bright,\nKai’s light dims into the night.\n\n[chorus]\nHush now, little firefly,\nDrift and dream beneath the sky.\nColors fade, the night is deep,\nTime to rest, time to sleep.\n\n[verse]\nBranch holds him, safe and near,\nWhispers sing for him to hear.\nClose your eyes, let go, let be,\nMorning comes so patiently.\n\n[chorus]\nHush now, little firefly,\nDrift and dream beneath the sky.\nColors fade, the night is deep,\nTime to rest, time to sleep.",
