      type: "long_story",
      title: "Lila and the Starry Seed",
      description: "When a tiny silver seed drifts through Lila’s window on a moonbeam, she plants it in her nightlight’s glow—and watches in awe as it grows into a shimmering staircase to the stars. But the real magic begins when the staircase starts to bloom with glowing flowers that hum lullabies only she can hear.",
      cover: "/covers/gen-9d8e3f91919c.svg",
      addedAt: "2026-03-10",
      mood: "curious",
      story_type: "dream",
      text: "[GENTLE] Lila loved the night. While the house slept, she would tiptoe to her window and press her nose against the cool glass. [CURIOUS] Outside, the sky was a deep, velvety blue, sprinkled with stars that twinkled like tiny lanterns. [JOYFUL] 'Hello, little lights,' she would whisper, waving at the moon. [laugh] The moon always waved back, its silver glow dancing on her fingertips.\n\n[ADVENTUROUS] One evening, as Lila watched the stars, something strange happened. A single silver seed, no bigger than a pea, floated through her window on a moonbeam. [EXCITED] It spun in slow circles, as if it were dancing just for her. [WHISPERING] 'Oh!' Lila gasped. She reached out, and the seed landed softly in her palm. It was warm, like a tiny sun.\n\n[CURIOUS] Lila didn’t know what to do with the seed. So, she did what she always did with special things—she placed it in her favorite blue nightlight. The nightlight glowed softly, casting a circle of golden light on her floor. [MYSTERIOUS] Lila curled up beside it, watching the seed. 'Maybe you’ll grow into something wonderful,' she murmured. [DRAMATIC_PAUSE] And then, she waited.\n\n[EXCITED] At first, nothing happened. But then, the seed began to tremble. A tiny sprout pushed its way out, reaching toward the light. [JOYFUL] Lila clapped her hands. 'It’s growing!' The sprout twisted and turned, growing taller and taller, until it touched the ceiling. [ADVENTUROUS] But it didn’t stop there. The sprout kept growing, stretching out of her window and up, up, up into the night sky.\n\n[CURIOUS] Lila stood on her tiptoes and peered out the window. The sprout had become a shimmering staircase, winding its way through the stars. [MYSTERIOUS] And at the very top, where the staircase met the sky, something was glowing. [DRAMATIC_PAUSE] It looked like a door made of starlight.\n\n[EXCITED] Lila didn’t hesitate. She climbed onto the first step, and the staircase held her gently, as if it had been waiting for her all along. [ADVENTUROUS] Up she went, higher and higher, past twinkling stars and swirling galaxies. The air smelled sweet, like honey and rain, and the stars hummed a soft, sleepy song.\n\n[GENTLE] The staircase was soft beneath Lila’s feet. It felt like walking on clouds, light and warm. [CALM] The stars around her glowed steadily, their light pulsing like a slow, steady heartbeat. She climbed higher, and the world below grew smaller and smaller, until her house looked like a tiny toy nestled in the dark.\n\n[GENTLE] The air was still. No wind, no sound, just the quiet hum of the stars. [CALM] Lila reached out and touched one. It was cool and smooth, like a pebble from a river. The star shimmered at her touch, as if it were saying hello.\n\n[MYSTERIOUS] As she climbed, the staircase began to change. Tiny buds appeared along the steps, glowing faintly in the dark. [GENTLE] They unfurled slowly, petal by petal, until they bloomed into flowers made of starlight. The flowers hummed the same soft song Lila had heard before, and their light filled the air with a golden glow.\n\n[CALM] Lila sat down on a step and watched the flowers bloom. They swayed gently, as if they were dancing to the music. [GENTLE] She plucked one and held it to her ear. The hum grew louder, wrapping around her like a cozy blanket. It was the sound of the stars singing, and it made her feel safe and warm.\n\n[CALM] The staircase stretched on, higher and higher, but Lila didn’t feel tired. The air was cool and sweet, and the stars kept her company. [GENTLE] She leaned back against the steps and watched the flowers glow. Their light flickered like fireflies, casting soft shadows on the staircase. The shadows danced and swayed, playing a quiet game of tag.\n\n[CALM] Time seemed to slow. The stars above twinkled lazily, and the flowers hummed their lullaby. [GENTLE] Lila’s eyelids grew heavy. The staircase felt softer now, like a bed made of clouds. She curled up on the steps, and the flowers leaned in close, their petals brushing against her cheek like a gentle kiss.\n\n[CALM] The air was still. The stars were still. The world was still. [GENTLE] Lila closed her eyes and listened to the hum of the flowers. It was the sound of the night singing her to sleep.\n\n[SLEEPY] The stars hummed softly. The flowers glowed warm.\n\n[WHISPERING] Lila’s breathing slowed. The staircase cradled her gently.\n\n[SLEEPY] The air was still. The light was soft. The world was quiet.\n\n[WHISPERING] The stars wrapped her in their glow. The flowers sang her a lullaby.\n\n[SLEEPY] Her eyes closed. Her body relaxed. The night held her close.\n\n[WHISPERING] Safe... and warm... and still...\n\n[SLEEPY] The stars hummed... the flowers glowed... the staircase slept...\n\n[WHISPERING] Shh... shh... shh...",
      character: {"name": "Lila", "identity": "A dreamy stargazer who believes in magic", "special": "She can hear the secret songs the stars sing at night", "personality_tags": ["Dreamy", "Curious"]},
