      mood: "curious",
      story_type: "folk_tale",
      text: "[GENTLE] High above the snowy Arctic, where the world was quiet and white, lived a little snow sprite named Aria. She had wings like frost and a heart full of dreams.\n\n[CURIOUS] One night, as she floated on a gentle breeze, she heard something magical. A soft, singing sound came from the sky. It was the aurora, dancing and humming a sweet tune.\n\n[EXCITED] Aria’s eyes sparkled. She had never heard anything so beautiful! She fluttered closer, her frost wings shimmering in the starlight. The aurora’s song grew louder, wrapping around her like a cozy blanket.\n\n[WHISPERING] 'Come closer,' the aurora seemed to whisper. Aria drifted higher, her tiny hands reaching toward the glowing lights. The song filled her heart with warmth, even in the cold Arctic night.\n\n[JOYFUL] She laughed as the aurora swirled around her, painting the sky with colors of green, pink, and blue. The song was a lullaby, gentle and kind, like the world was tucking her in.\n\n[SLEEPY] Aria closed her eyes, still floating among the stars. The aurora’s song softened, carrying her into a dream where the sky sang forever, and she was part of its melody.",
