      text: "[GENTLE] High above the world, where the sky is soft and the stars hum lullabies, there lived a little moon named Luna. She was round and warm, like a cozy hug in the night sky, and she loved watching over the village of Whispering Hollow. Every evening, as the sun dipped below the hills, Luna would rise, her silver light spilling over the rooftops like melted butter.\n\n[CURIOUS] But tonight, something was different. The lanterns in Whispering Hollow—those little glowing friends that lined the cobblestone streets—were flickering weakly, as if they were tired. Luna tilted her head, her light shimmering with concern. \"Oh dear,\" she whispered to the wind, \"what’s happening down there?\"\n\n[ADVENTUROUS] Without a second thought, Luna began to drift downward, her silver glow stretching like a ribbon toward the village. The closer she came, the more she noticed: the lanterns weren’t just tired—they were lonely. Their flames danced sadly, as if they missed something important. Luna’s heart ached. She had to help.\n\n[JOYFUL] As she floated over the first lantern, she reached out with her light, brushing it gently. \"Hello, little one,\" she murmured. The lantern’s flame flickered brighter, as if waking from a dream. [laugh] \"You remember now, don’t you?\" Luna said softly. The lantern glowed a little stronger, and Luna smiled. She drifted to the next one, and the next, her light weaving through the streets like a silver thread.\n\n[MYSTERIOUS] Then, she heard it—a soft, whispery sound, like leaves rustling secrets. It was coming from the heart of the village, where the oldest lantern of all stood guard over the town square. Luna’s glow pulsed with curiosity. What was that sound? And why did the lanterns seem to lean toward it, as if listening?\n\n[EXCITED] She floated closer, her light dancing over the cobblestones. The oldest lantern’s flame was barely a spark, but it trembled with excitement. \"Luna,\" it seemed to say, \"we’ve been waiting for you.\" And with that, the whispery sound grew louder, swirling around her like a warm breeze. It was the sound of the village’s forgotten magic—the magic of belonging.\n\n[CALM] Luna settled into the rhythm of the village. The air smelled of cinnamon and woodsmoke, and the cobblestones were cool beneath her light. She drifted from lantern to lantern, her silver glow wrapping around each one like a blanket. The flames grew brighter, their light steady and warm. The village sighed, as if remembering something beautiful.\n\n[GENTLE] The oldest lantern in the square glowed the brightest of all. Its flame was no longer a spark but a steady, golden heart. Luna rested her light against it, and the lantern hummed softly, like a lullaby. The sound spread through the streets, carried by the breeze, and the other lanterns joined in. Their flames danced together, weaving a tapestry of light and warmth.\n\n[MYSTERIOUS] The whispery sound swirled around Luna, wrapping her in its warmth. It was the sound of the village’s stories—the laughter of children, the clinking of teacups, the rustle of pages in a well-loved book. The lanterns remembered now. They remembered the magic of being together, of lighting the way for one another.\n\n[CALM] Luna’s light softened, her glow melting into the lanterns’ flames. The village was quiet, but it wasn’t still. It was alive with the hum of belonging, with the steady, sure beat of hearts that knew they were home. The air was soft. The light was soft. The night was soft.\n\n[GENTLE] The cobblestones gleamed under the lanterns’ glow, their edges smoothed by time and care. The breeze carried the scent of autumn—crisp apples, damp leaves, and the faintest hint of woodsmoke. Luna closed her eyes (or at least, she imagined she did) and let the warmth of the village wrap around her. She was part of it now, part of the magic.\n\n[SLEEPY] The lanterns glowed softly. Their flames were steady. The village was still.\n\n[WHISPERING] Luna’s light melted into the night. The stars hummed their lullabies. The wind carried the sound of dreams.\n\n[SLEEPY] The cobblestones were cool. The air was warm. The world was quiet.\n\n[WHISPERING] The lanterns remembered. They glowed together, their light a promise. Safe. Warm. Still.\n\n[SLEEPY] Luna drifted upward, her silver glow fading into the sky. The village slept beneath her, wrapped in light and love.\n\n[WHISPERING] The stars twinkled softly. The moon watched over them all. The night was gentle.\n\n[SLEEPY] Close your eyes. The lanterns are glowing. The village is safe.\n\n[WHISPERING] Safe... and warm... and still...",
