      text: "[GENTLE] Mira had a paintbrush that never ran out of paint, but she was terrible at staying on the ground. \n\n[JOYFUL] Every afternoon, she’d leap onto the back of a wobbly cloud named Puff, who was *very* afraid of heights. [laugh] 'Hold on tight!' Mira would giggle as Puff trembled like a bowl of jelly. \n\n[CURIOUS] One day, they spotted a rainbow lying flat on the horizon, its colors faded to gray. 'Oh no!' Mira gasped. 'It’s lost its sparkle!' Puff gulped. 'We’ll have to fly *up* to fix it?' \n\n[ADVENTUROUS] Mira dipped her brush into a puddle of golden light and swirled it across the sky. [DRAMATIC_PAUSE] The rainbow shimmered—then sneezed! [laugh] 'Who tickled my stripes?' it giggled. \n\n[GENTLE] Puff, still wobbling, floated closer. 'I think we need *all* the colors,' he whispered. Together, they painted the sky with swirls of red, blue, and green until the rainbow glowed brighter than ever. \n\n[WHISPERING] 'You did it,' Mira said, hugging Puff’s fluffy side. The cloud sighed happily. 'Maybe heights aren’t so scary when you’re not alone.' \n\n[SLEEPY] As the sun dipped low, the sky turned soft and pink. Mira curled up on Puff’s warmest spot, her paintbrush tucked under her arm. The rainbow hummed a quiet tune, and the clouds drifted gently home.",
      character: {"name": "Mira", "identity": "A fearless little artist who paints the sky with joy", "special": "Her paintbrush brings color to anything—even a cloud’s worries", "personality_tags": ["Creative", "Playful"]},
