      mood: "calm",
      story_type: "folk_tale",
      text: "[GENTLE] Hush, hush, little Rosie,\nsoft in the golden light.\nLeaves so green, so still, so sweet,\nwarm breeze sings just right.\n\n[CALM] Shh, shh, the garden hums,\na tune so soft and low.\nRosie breathes the scent so deep,\nwhere the summer roses grow.\n\n[CURIOUS] Oh, what’s that in the air so sweet?\nA whisper, soft and new.\nThe wind brings smells of earth and rain,\na change is coming through.\n\n[WHISPERING] 'Stay, stay,' the old oak tree sighs,\n'but seasons turn, my dear.'\nRosie nods, her leaves so small,\n'Then I’ll grow right here.'\n\n[JOYFUL] And so she waits, and so she grows,\nthrough sun and rain and breeze.\nHer scent stays soft, her roots stay strong,\na home in every season’s ease.\n\n[SLEEPY] Hush now, Rosie, close your leaves,\ndream of golden light.\nThe garden hums a lullaby,\nand all is calm and bright.",
