      type: "story",
      title: "Mira and the Colors of the Dark",
      description: "Deep beneath the roots of an ancient tree, a hidden cave glows with shifting colors no one else can see. Mira, who fears the [EMPHASIS]dark[/EMPHASIS], must sit very still to discover its [SAFETY]gentle secret[/SAFETY].",
      cover: "/covers/gen-ee66b4718ed1.svg",
      addedAt: "2026-03-19",
      mood: "anxious",
      story_type: "dream",
      text: "[GENTLE] Mira’s fingers trembled as she curled them into the hem of her nightgown. The [EMPHASIS]dark[/EMPHASIS] pressed against her skin like a cold whisper, and her heart beat so loudly she was sure it would wake the whole house. She had counted every crack in the ceiling, every creak of the floorboards, but sleep still felt far away.\n\n[CURIOUS] Then she noticed it—a soft glow seeping through a crack in the floorboards. It wasn’t the yellow light of the moon or the flicker of fireflies. It was something else, something [SAFETY]warm[/SAFETY] and shifting, like a living rainbow. Mira held her breath. What if it was a trick? What if it vanished the moment she moved?\n\n[DRAMATIC_PAUSE] She pressed her palm to the floor and felt the wood give way just a little. The crack widened, and the light spilled out like water. Without thinking, she slipped her fingers into the gap and pulled. The floorboards lifted, revealing a narrow staircase spiraling downward into the earth.\n\n[MYSTERIOUS] The air smelled of damp stone and something sweet, like crushed petals. Mira’s knees wobbled as she stepped onto the first stair, but the colors below called to her. Pinks melted into blues, blues into golds, swirling together in a dance she could almost hear. She took another step, then another, until she stood in the heart of the cave, surrounded by light.\n\n[JOYFUL] The walls weren’t dark at all. They were covered in tiny, glowing crystals, each one pulsing with its own color. Some sparkled like stars, others shimmered like dewdrops. Mira reached out and touched one, and it hummed softly against her fingertip. The [EMPHASIS]dark[/EMPHASIS] wasn’t empty. It was full of stories, waiting to be seen.\n\n[WHISPERING] A voice, soft as a breeze, seemed to say, *You’re safe here.* Mira looked around but saw no one. The crystals glowed brighter, as if they were listening. She sat down in the middle of the cave, cross-legged, and let the colors wash over her. The fear didn’t disappear, but it didn’t feel so heavy anymore.\n\n[SLEEPY] When Mira finally climbed back up the stairs, the crack in the floor sealed itself behind her. She curled into bed, her eyelids growing heavier with each blink. The colors lingered in her mind, a quiet promise that the [SAFETY]dark[/SAFETY] was never as empty as it seemed. And for the first time in a long time, she drifted off without a single [EMPHASIS]what if[/EMPHASIS] keeping her awake.",
      character: {"name": "Mira", "identity": "A quiet observer who notices the magic hiding in plain sight", "special": "She can see colors in the dark that others miss", "personality_tags": ["Gentle", "Curious"]},
      target_age: 7,
