      story_type: "folk_tale",
      text: "[GENTLE] The sun was slipping behind the hills, painting the sky in soft pinks and oranges. [CURIOUS] Lulla, a little sparrow with feathers the color of warm honey, perched on the lowest branch of the old apple tree. She tilted her head, listening. [EXCITED] There it was again—the whispering song of the wheat fields! A soft, rustling melody that only she could hear.\n\n[ADVENTUROUS] 'Mama! Papa! The wheat is singing!' Lulla chirped, fluttering her wings. [JOYFUL] Her family was scattered across the garden—Mama was gathering seeds near the sunflowers, Papa was teaching her little brothers how to fly, and Grandma was dozing in the shade. [CURIOUS] 'It’s the most beautiful sound,' Lulla said, hopping from foot to foot. 'We have to listen together!'\n\n[MYSTERIOUS] The wind carried the song closer, wrapping around Lulla like a cozy blanket. [EXCITED] 'Hurry!' she called to her family. 'The wheat is waiting!' [laugh] Her little brothers giggled as they tumbled through the air, their tiny wings still wobbly. [GENTLE] Mama smiled and ruffled Lulla’s feathers. 'Lead the way, little one,' she said.\n\n[ADVENTUROUS] Lulla took off, darting between the tall stalks of wheat. The song grew louder, sweeter, filling the air with warmth. [CURIOUS] The wheat swayed gently, as if dancing to the music. [DRAMATIC_PAUSE] ...And then, Lulla saw something magical. [EXCITED] Tiny fireflies were flickering in the wheat, their lights blinking in time with the song!\n\n[JOYFUL] 'Look!' Lulla chirped. 'The fireflies are singing too!' [chuckle] Her family gathered around, their eyes wide with wonder. [GENTLE] The golden fields stretched out before them, alive with music and light. [WHISPERING] 'This is our song,' Lulla whispered. 'A song for all of us.'\n\n[CALM] The wheat swayed softly, brushing against Lulla’s feathers like a gentle hug. [GENTLE] The air was warm, filled with the scent of earth and summer. The fireflies glowed brighter, their light dancing on the tips of the wheat stalks. [CALM] Lulla closed her eyes and listened. The song was everywhere—inside her, around her, part of her.\n\n[GENTLE] Mama perched beside her, her wings wrapped around Lulla’s shoulders. [CALM] 'Do you feel it?' Mama whispered. 'The song is in the wind, in the wheat, in us.' [GENTLE] Lulla nodded, her heart full. The music was like a soft blanket, wrapping them all together.\n\n[CALM] Papa and the little ones settled into the wheat, their feathers rustling softly. [GENTLE] Grandma hummed along, her voice low and sweet. The fireflies flickered above them, their lights like tiny stars. [CALM] The world was quiet, except for the song. The song was everything.\n\n[GENTLE] The wheat was soft beneath Lulla’s feet. The air was soft against her face. The light was soft, golden, and warm. [CALM] The song wrapped around them like a lullaby, slow and steady. [GENTLE] Lulla’s wings grew heavy. Her eyelids fluttered. The music carried her, safe and warm.\n\n[CALM] The fireflies dimmed, their light fading into the twilight. The wheat stopped swaying, still and quiet. [GENTLE] The song softened, becoming a whisper, then a sigh. [CALM] The world was still. The world was soft. The world was home.\n\n[SLEEPY] The wheat was still. The wind was still. The song was still.\n\n[WHISPERING] Lulla’s feathers were warm. Her family was close. The night was soft.\n\n[SLEEPY] The fireflies slept. The stars blinked. The moon smiled.\n\n[WHISPERING] Close your eyes. Feel the song. Safe and warm.\n\n[SLEEPY] The wheat hums. The night sighs. The world sleeps.\n\n[WHISPERING] Safe... warm... still...\n\n[SLEEPY] mmm...",
