      id: "gen-473198145b30",
      type: "story",
      title: "Bubble and the Lonely Comet",
      description: "High above the clouds, where stars hum lullabies, a tiny jellyfish drifts through the cosmos, missing the friend who once swam beside her. Then, one night, a comet with a broken tail glows softly nearby—but it’s not the same, and that’s okay.",
      cover: "/covers/gen-473198145b30.svg",
      addedAt: "2026-03-21",
      mood: "sad",
      story_type: "folk_tale",
      text: "[GENTLE] Bubble the jellyfish had always floated through the starry sky with her best friend, Splash. They would dance between the planets, their glowing tendrils weaving through the dark like silver threads. But now Splash was [EMPHASIS]gone[/EMPHASIS], and the sky felt wider, colder, and so [EMPHASIS]empty[/EMPHASIS].\n\n[CALM] Tonight, Bubble drifted near Saturn’s rings, watching the ice crystals sparkle. She traced the same path they’d taken together, her light flickering weakly. The silence was louder than the hum of the stars. [WHISPERING] 'I miss you,' she whispered, though no one was there to hear.\n\n[MYSTERIOUS] Then, a soft glow caught her eye. A small comet, its tail fractured and dim, hovered nearby. It didn’t speak, but its light pulsed gently, like a heartbeat. [CURIOUS] Bubble tilted her head. The comet wasn’t Splash. It wasn’t her friend at all. But it was there.\n\n[JOYFUL] Slowly, Bubble reached out a tendril. The comet’s glow warmed her, just a little. They floated together, not saying anything, just sharing the quiet. The sky still felt big, but it wasn’t [EMPHASIS]alone[/EMPHASIS] anymore.\n\n[SLEEPY] And that was enough. Bubble closed her eyes, letting the comet’s light wrap around her like a blanket. The stars hummed on, and for now, she was drifting—safe, and softly held.",
      character: {"name": "Bubble", "identity": "A gentle jellyfish who glows with the memories of her friend", "special": "Her tendrils shimmer with stardust when she’s happy or sad", "personality_tags": ["Gentle", "Dreamy"]},
