      description: "When a bubbly little cloud named Zizzle discovers she can change colors by sneezing, she sets off on a giggly adventure across the night sky—until she meets a comet who smells like cinnamon and teaches her that being perfectly imperfect is the best magic of all.",
      cover: "/covers/gen-4277697b337e.svg",
      addedAt: "2026-03-22",
      mood: "wired",
      story_type: "folk_tale",
      text: "[GENTLE] High above the sleepy world, where the stars twinkled like tiny night-lights, there lived a little cloud named Zizzle.\n\n[JOYFUL] Zizzle was the silliest cloud in the whole sky. She loved to bounce on moonbeams and tickle the tops of mountains. But her very favorite thing? Sneezing! [EMPHASIS]ACHOOOOO![/EMPHASIS]\n\n[EXCITED] One night, Zizzle sneezed—and something magical happened. Instead of white, she turned [EMPHASIS]sooooo pink![/EMPHASIS] Then purple! Then green with yellow polka dots! Zizzle giggled. \"I’m a rainbow cloud!\"\n\n[ADVENTUROUS] She zoomed through the sky, sneezing and changing colors. [EMPHASIS]ACHOO—BLUE! ACHOO—ORANGE![/EMPHASIS] But then—[DRAMATIC_PAUSE]—she sneezed too hard and [EMPHASIS]SPLAT![/EMPHASIS] crashed into a comet named Cinnamon.\n\n[CURIOUS] Cinnamon smelled like warm cinnamon rolls (which Zizzle loved). \"You’re a very… bouncy cloud,\" Cinnamon chuckled. \"But why do you keep sneezing?\"\n\n[GENTLE] Zizzle sighed. \"I just wanted to be special. But I’m too silly and sneezy!\"\n\n[WHISPERING] Cinnamon smiled. \"Silly is wonderful. And sneezes? They make the best rainbows.\" [laugh] Zizzle giggled. Maybe she didn’t need to be perfect—just perfectly *her*.\n\n[SLEEPY] The two friends floated together, watching the stars blink sleepily. Zizzle’s colors softened to a cozy lavender, and the night wrapped around them like a snuggly blanket. The sky was quiet. The stars hummed. And Zizzle? She drifted… drifted… into the sweetest dreams.",
