      text: "[GENTLE] Finn the little sand dragon curled up in his hollow beneath the dune. His scales prickled, his breath came quick. The desert was never quiet at twilight, but tonight the sounds felt too loud—like the wind was whispering his name.\n\n[CURIOUS] He pressed his ear to the warm sand. The grains hummed softly, a tune he almost recognized. 'What if the dunes don’t like me?' he thought. 'What if I step wrong and they swallow me whole?' The thoughts kept coming, one after another, like waves.\n\n[MYSTERIOUS] Then, a voice—soft as a breeze—drifted up from the sand. 'Finn… we’ve been waiting.' The dune ahead shimmered, and a tiny sand fox with golden eyes blinked up at him. 'You’re afraid of us?' she asked. [WHISPERING] 'We only sing to those who listen.'\n\n[JOYFUL] Finn’s heart slowed. The fox’s paws pattered across the sand, and the dunes hummed louder, happier now. 'You’re not warnings,' Finn realized. 'You’re stories.' The desert wasn’t trying to scare him—it was inviting him to dance.\n\n[CALM] Hand in paw, Finn and the fox drifted over the singing sands. The whispers wrapped around him like a blanket, warm and safe. The moon rose, steady and bright, just like it would tomorrow night.\n\n[SLEEPY] Finn curled up again, this time with the fox nestled beside him. The desert hummed him to sleep, and for the first time, the sounds didn’t feel loud at all. They felt like home.",
