      type: "story",
      title: "Stella and the Shrinking Starbeam",
      description: "When a tiny star named Stella tumbles into a village square, she discovers she can shrink herself—but now she’s stuck! A curious child named Milo helps her find her way home, one giggle at a time. Together, they learn that even the brightest lights need a little help sometimes.",
      cover: "/covers/gen-6134b0c7424e.svg",
      addedAt: "2026-03-27",
      mood: "wired",
      story_type: "fable",
      text: "[GENTLE] One day, a little star named Stella said to the evening sky—\n\n[JOYFUL] 'I wonder what it’s like to be small enough to fit in a pocket!' [CURIOUS] And with a tiny [EMPHASIS]poof[/EMPHASIS], she shrank herself down, down, down—until she tumbled right out of the sky and landed in a village square.\n\n[EXCITED] The world looked so big now! The cobblestones were like boulders, and the lampposts stretched taller than the moon. [laugh] Stella tried to bounce, but she just went [EMPHASIS]boing[/EMPHASIS] into a pile of leaves. 'Oh dear,' she sighed. 'I don’t think I can reach the sky from here.'\n\n[WHISPERING] Just then, a small voice said, 'Are you a firefly?' [CURIOUS] Stella turned to see a boy named Milo, his eyes wide. 'No,' she giggled. 'I’m a star! But I might need a ladder.'\n\n[ADVENTUROUS] Milo grinned. 'I have an idea!' He scooped her up and carried her to the top of the clock tower, where the wind hummed a soft tune. [DRAMATIC_PAUSE] But Stella still couldn’t reach the sky—her glow was too small now.\n\n[GENTLE] 'Maybe,' Milo said, 'you don’t have to be big to shine.' [JOYFUL] And so Stella twinkled right where she was, lighting up the village square with tiny, perfect sparkles. The fireflies danced around her, and the children clapped.\n\n[SLEEPY] As the stars blinked awake above, Stella curled into Milo’s palm, warm and content. She didn’t need to be big to be exactly where she belonged.",
